17 (2) 'Peer-to-peer car-sharing' shall have the same meaning as provided in Code
18 Section 40-1-220.
19 (3) 'Rental agreement' means an agreement under which a motor vehicle without a driver
20 is rented or leased to a consumer for a period of 90 days or less. Such term shall not
21 include a peer-to-peer car-sharing arrangement.
22 (b) It shall be an unlawful unfair or deceptive trade practice for any motor vehicle rental
23 company to refuse to rent or lease a motor vehicle under a rental agreement to an individual
24 who is 25 years of age or older solely on the basis of the individual's age, provided that
25 such individual holds a valid driver's license authorizing such individual to operate such
26 motor vehicle on public roads within this state and such individual has, or is able to obtain
27 through the motor vehicle rental company or otherwise, an insurance policy that would
28 apply to such individual's use of such motor vehicle and that would provide at least the
29 minimum coverages required by law.
30 (c) Any person who violates this Code section shall be subject to the penalties provided
31 for in this part."
32 SECTION 2.
33 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
